WEBVTT

00:05.005 --> 00:08.051
-[THEME SONG PLAYING]

00:12.795 --> 00:15.798
-♪ SOME PEOPLE STAND
IN THE DARKNESS ♪

00:16.929 --> 00:20.846
♪ AFRAID TO STEP
INTO THE LIGHT ♪

00:21.021 --> 00:24.459
♪ SOME PEOPLE NEED
TO HAVE SOMEBODY ♪

00:24.633 --> 00:27.897
♪ WHEN THE EDGE
OF SURRENDER'S IN SIGHT ♪

00:28.071 --> 00:30.726
♪ DON'T YOU WORRY ♪

00:31.422 --> 00:34.208
♪ IT'S GONNA BE ALL RIGHT ♪

00:36.949 --> 00:38.734
♪ 'CAUSE I'M ALWAYS READY ♪

00:38.908 --> 00:41.563
♪ I WON'T LET YOU
OUT OF MY SIGHT ♪

00:45.306 --> 00:47.743
-♪ I'LL BE READY ♪

00:47.917 --> 00:49.266
-♪ I'LL BE READY ♪

00:49.440 --> 00:51.312
-♪ NEVER YOU FEAR ♪

00:51.486 --> 00:53.270
-♪ NO, DON'T YOU FEAR ♪

00:53.444 --> 00:56.012
-♪ I'LL BE READY ♪

00:56.795 --> 00:59.624
-♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS ♪

00:59.798 --> 01:02.236
♪ I'M ALWAYS HERE ♪

01:20.993 --> 01:22.647
♪ 'CAUSE I'M ALWAYS READY ♪

01:22.821 --> 01:26.129
♪ I WON'T LET YOU
OUT OF MY SIGHT ♪

01:27.739 --> 01:28.827
♪ OH ♪

01:29.001 --> 01:31.830
-♪ I'LL BE READY ♪

01:32.004 --> 01:33.528
-♪ I'LL BE READY ♪

01:33.702 --> 01:35.399
-♪ NEVER YOU FEAR ♪

01:35.573 --> 01:37.488
-♪ NO, DON'T YOU FEAR ♪

01:37.662 --> 01:40.361
-♪ I'LL BE READY ♪

01:40.535 --> 01:43.581
-♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS ♪

01:43.755 --> 01:46.889
♪ I'M ALWAYS HERE ♪

02:20.792 --> 02:23.099
-[BOTH LAUGHING]

02:42.945 --> 02:44.338
-WHAT ARE YOU WAITING FOR?

02:44.512 --> 02:46.209
THE SUN'S ALMOST UP.

03:13.410 --> 03:16.587
-MMM. I FEEL ALIVE
FOR THE FIRST TIME IN YEARS.

03:20.374 --> 03:21.810
-KISS ME UNDERWATER.

03:44.920 --> 03:46.443
-[MUFFLED SCREAMS]

05:00.691 --> 05:02.171
-SO WHY DON'T
YOU BRING KIM?

05:02.345 --> 05:03.999
-KELLY. HER NAME IS KELLY.
-WHATEVER.

05:04.565 --> 05:05.914
-NO CHEMISTRY.
-NO CHEMISTRY?

05:06.088 --> 05:07.568
WHAT'S WRONG WITH YOU?
SHE WAS GORGEOUS.

05:07.742 --> 05:08.743
-SHE WAS GORGEOUS,
BUT THERE WAS NO CHEMISTRY.

05:08.917 --> 05:09.961
-AH, MITCH.

05:10.135 --> 05:11.485
YOU KNOW WHAT
YOUR PROBLEM IS?

05:11.659 --> 05:13.095
SINCE YOUR DIVORCE,
YOU'VE BECOME CAUTIOUS.

05:14.705 --> 05:16.707
-I GOT HOBIE TO CONSIDER.

05:16.881 --> 05:18.405
I DON'T WANT HIM
GETTING ATTACHED TO ANYBODY
I'M NOT SERIOUS ABOUT.

05:18.579 --> 05:20.885
-OH, HE CAN HANDLE IT.
I THINK YOU'RE THE ONE

05:21.059 --> 05:22.322
WHO'S AFRAID
OF GETTING ATTACHED.

05:23.105 --> 05:24.802
SOONER OR LATER,
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE TO OPEN UP.

06:45.492 --> 06:47.145
-[CAR HONKS]

07:30.841 --> 07:32.277
-[SCREAMS]

07:43.854 --> 07:45.116
-CALL IT IN.

07:45.290 --> 07:46.422
RENZO, TAKE IT.

07:46.596 --> 07:47.684
-RESCUE IN PROGRESS.

07:47.858 --> 07:49.817
CAR SUBMERGED
OFF TOWER 19.

07:49.991 --> 07:51.993
REPEAT-- 10-25,
TOWER 19.

09:01.889 --> 09:04.065
-[COUGHS]
-THAT'S GOOD.
SPIT IT OUT.

09:04.239 --> 09:05.762
THAT'S GOOD.
OKAY...

09:05.936 --> 09:07.285
OKAY...

09:12.073 --> 09:13.640
TAKE IT EASY.
TAKE IT EASY.

09:15.032 --> 09:16.468
-IS HE DEAD?

09:17.687 --> 09:18.558
IS HE DEAD?

09:19.167 --> 09:20.342
NO!
-I'M SORRY.

09:20.516 --> 09:22.213
-[SOBBING]

09:35.052 --> 09:35.923
-HOW'S EVERYTHING?

09:36.097 --> 09:37.577
-WELL, SHE'S A LUCKY LADY.

09:39.796 --> 09:40.623
-HOW YOU FEELING?

09:41.581 --> 09:42.494
-OKAY.

09:43.234 --> 09:44.496
-YOU MIND
IF I CHECK YOUR PULSE?

09:47.108 --> 09:48.196
STRONG.

09:49.240 --> 09:50.938
-WELL, I'M SURE EVERY
WOMAN'S PULSE IS STRONG
WHEN YOU TAKE IT.

09:51.112 --> 09:52.766
-I DON'T KNOW ABOUT THAT.

09:53.636 --> 09:55.116
BUT I DO NEED TO KNOW
SOME INFORMATION

09:55.290 --> 09:56.900
ABOUT WHAT HAPPENED
ON THE ROAD BACK THERE.

09:58.902 --> 09:59.773
-UM...

10:00.687 --> 10:02.036
STEVE WAS DRIVING
ME TO THE MARINA.

10:02.210 --> 10:03.254
TO MY BOAT.

10:04.212 --> 10:06.475
-CAN YOU GIVE ME
SPECIFIC INFORMATION?

10:06.649 --> 10:07.563
I MEAN,
THERE WAS NO I.D.

10:07.737 --> 10:09.217
-UM, I KNOW.
HE WAS...

10:10.044 --> 10:11.567
HE WAS GOING
TO THE BEACH RIGHT AFTER.

10:14.135 --> 10:17.094
STEVE WAS, UH...
WE WERE IN BUSINESS TOGETHER.

10:17.268 --> 10:18.922
HE WAS MY PARTNER.

10:20.620 --> 10:23.971
ANYWAY, I DON'T REALLY
KNOW WHAT HAPPENED.

10:25.842 --> 10:27.888
I MUST HAVE DOZED OFF
IN THE PASSENGER SEAT.

10:28.671 --> 10:30.020
AND BEFORE I KNEW IT...

10:30.194 --> 10:32.632
WATER WAS RUSHING IN
ALL OVER THE PLACE.

10:36.244 --> 10:36.984
I'M SORRY.

10:37.158 --> 10:38.028
-NO, NO.

10:38.594 --> 10:39.464
IT'S OKAY.

10:41.641 --> 10:43.686
CAN I BRING
YOU SOMETHING MISS...

10:43.860 --> 10:45.470
-ALLISON.
PLEASE, UM...

10:46.558 --> 10:47.472
COFFEE WOULD BE NICE.

10:47.647 --> 10:48.952
-OKAY.

10:50.693 --> 10:51.955
OH! UM...

10:52.129 --> 10:54.044
UNFORTUNATELY,
THERE ARE SOME PROCEDURES

10:54.218 --> 10:57.265
THAT HAVE GOTTA BE DONE
BEFORE WE CAN RELEASE YOU.

10:58.048 --> 10:59.093
-OH. LIKE WHAT?

10:59.876 --> 11:01.356
-WELL, A POLICE REPORT,
FOR ONE.

11:01.530 --> 11:03.010
THERE'S AN OFFICER WAITING
FOR YOU UPSTAIRS.

11:04.402 --> 11:05.708
-OH. UH...

11:07.536 --> 11:09.320
I DON'T THINK
I'M REALLY UP TO IT TODAY.

11:09.494 --> 11:11.714
DO YOU THINK IT COULD
WAIT TILL TOMORROW?

11:13.716 --> 11:14.674
PLEASE?

11:17.764 --> 11:18.678
-I'LL SEE
WHAT I CAN DO.

11:19.635 --> 11:20.592
-THANKS.

11:20.767 --> 11:23.465
-OKAY.
-THANKS FOR EVERYTHING.

11:25.293 --> 11:26.163
-CREAM AND SUGAR?

11:27.034 --> 11:27.991
-BLACK.

11:28.165 --> 11:29.166
-OKAY.

11:35.129 --> 11:35.956
-[DOOR CLOSES]

12:04.941 --> 12:07.117
-SHE GAVE ME ALL THE INFORMATION
SHE COULD REMEMBER,

12:07.291 --> 12:08.815
SO I PUT IT ALL
IN THIS REPORT.

12:10.425 --> 12:12.122
SHE'S STILL PRETTY SHAKEN UP.

12:12.296 --> 12:14.908
-FROM WHAT SHAUNI TELLS ME,
"PRETTY" IS THE OPERATIVE WORD.

12:15.560 --> 12:16.910
-PRETTY DOESN'T
EVEN COME CLOSE.

12:17.432 --> 12:19.477
-YOU GAVE HER MOUTH-TO-MOUTH.
YOU OUGHT TO KNOW.

12:20.870 --> 12:22.524
-I GAVE YOU MOUTH-TO-MOUTH
ONCE, TOO.

12:22.698 --> 12:24.091
BELIEVE ME,
IT AIN'T THE SAME AS KISSING.

12:24.265 --> 12:25.657
-I KNOW, I KNOW.

12:25.832 --> 12:27.398
-SO YOU'LL DO ME A FAVOR?

12:27.572 --> 12:28.791
WAIT TILL TOMORROW?

12:29.661 --> 12:31.663
-SURE. THIS OUGHT TO
SUFFICE FOR NOW.

12:31.838 --> 12:33.709
-CORONER JUST
PICKED UP JOHN DOE.

12:34.449 --> 12:36.581
-SAYS HERE HIS NAME
IS STEVEN PIERCE?

12:36.756 --> 12:39.106
-YEAH? WELL MR. PIERCE
IS ONE WEIRD CORPSE.

12:39.280 --> 12:40.498
-WHY IS THAT?

12:40.672 --> 12:42.326
-HE WAS SUCKING UP WATER
LIKE A VACUUM.

12:43.893 --> 12:46.287
AND HE WAS DROWNING OUT
BEFORE WE EVEN HAD A CHANCE
TO RESUSCITATE HIM.

12:49.377 --> 12:51.727
SO... HOW'S THE LADY?

12:52.946 --> 12:55.600
-WELL, SHE'S PRETTY DISTRAUGHT,
BUT SHE CAME THROUGH
THE WHOLE THING OKAY.

12:56.993 --> 12:58.778
-SHE MUST HAVE
A GUARDIAN ANGEL.

13:18.145 --> 13:19.581
-READY?

13:27.110 --> 13:28.198
-DEFINITE CHEMISTRY.

13:28.372 --> 13:29.199
-WHAT?

13:30.461 --> 13:31.854
-DO YOU SUPPOSE
THERE'S ANY WAY

13:32.028 --> 13:33.508
I CAN GET MY STUFF
BEFORE TOMORROW?

13:34.770 --> 13:37.077
-NO. WE CAN'T GET A CRANE
TO LIFT IT OUT TILL THEN.

13:37.642 --> 13:39.079
-WELL, WHAT IF
SOMEBODY SAW THE CRASH

13:39.253 --> 13:41.037
AND THEY DIVE DOWN
AND TRY TO STEAL MY--

13:41.211 --> 13:42.952
-DON'T WORRY.
NOBODY'S GONNA GET IN THERE.

13:43.126 --> 13:44.736
YOUR TRUNK IS WEDGED
AGAINST THE BOTTOM.

13:45.825 --> 13:46.826
COME ON.

13:53.833 --> 13:54.703
-YEP. YEP.

14:23.384 --> 14:24.211
-ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

14:25.560 --> 14:26.430
-YEAH.

14:27.649 --> 14:29.694
I GUESS GETTING
IN A CAR AGAIN

14:29.869 --> 14:31.131
AND DRIVING
UP THE COAST...

14:32.088 --> 14:33.133
I THINK I'M SCARED.

14:34.177 --> 14:35.222
-IT'S OKAY.
I'LL DRIVE SLOW.

14:35.875 --> 14:37.877
-WHAT AM I GONNA DO
WHEN YOU DROP ME OFF AND LEAVE?

14:39.226 --> 14:40.096
-IS THERE SOMEBODY
YOU CAN CALL?

14:40.270 --> 14:41.228
-NO ONE.

14:42.142 --> 14:43.317
NO ONE I FEEL SAFE WITH...

14:43.883 --> 14:45.014
EXCEPT MY LIFEGUARD.

14:45.188 --> 14:46.798
I DON'T WANT
TO LET GO OF YOU.

14:47.669 --> 14:49.149
-IT'S GONNA BE PRETTY HARD
TO DRIVE THIS WAY.

14:50.106 --> 14:51.673
-SORRY.
-IT'S OKAY.

14:52.369 --> 14:53.283
IT'LL BE ALL RIGHT.

15:31.408 --> 15:32.844
THIS IS WHERE YOU LIVE?

15:33.019 --> 15:35.021
-I ONLY WISH
IT WAS MINE.

15:35.195 --> 15:36.413
IT BELONGS
TO ANOTHER INVESTOR.

15:36.587 --> 15:38.154
HE'S ON A PHOTO SAFARI
IN AFRICA.

15:38.328 --> 15:39.373
HE'S LETTING ME STAY HERE.

15:39.547 --> 15:40.374
COME ON IN.

15:48.991 --> 15:49.905
MAKE YOURSELF COMFORTABLE.

15:50.601 --> 15:51.428
-THANKS.

15:52.299 --> 15:53.517
-I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

15:57.347 --> 15:58.740
-[WHISTLES]

16:06.835 --> 16:08.358
-OPERATOR, PACIFIC PALISADES.

16:08.532 --> 16:10.099
CAN YOU CONNECT ME
TO WEST VIEW PATROL?

16:13.973 --> 16:17.454
HI, THERE'S A MAN
OUTSIDE 12973 HORIZON DRIVE.

16:17.628 --> 16:19.456
HE'S BEEN SITTING IN HIS CAR
FOR A COUPLE OF HOURS.

16:19.630 --> 16:21.806
WOULD YOU MIND SENDING SOMEONE
OVER TO CHECK IT OUT, PLEASE?

16:22.982 --> 16:23.939
THANK YOU.

16:51.532 --> 16:52.576
HOW DO YOU LIKE THE VIEW?

16:53.447 --> 16:54.578
-IT'S ABSOLUTELY...

16:55.492 --> 16:56.319
[GASPS]

16:57.973 --> 16:59.148
GORGEOUS.

16:59.322 --> 17:00.584
-I'LL GET US SOME DRINKS.

17:00.758 --> 17:01.629
I'LL BE RIGHT DOWN.

17:02.760 --> 17:03.674
-OKAY.

17:09.332 --> 17:10.203
-[BOTH LAUGHING]

17:10.768 --> 17:12.031
-YOU KNOW,
MY DAD TAUGHT ME TO SAIL.

17:12.204 --> 17:14.207
WE USED TO RUN
TRANSPACS TO HAWAII.

17:14.729 --> 17:17.558
I ONCE RACED SINGLE-HANDED
TO THE FARALLONS AND BACK.

17:18.211 --> 17:18.993
-NOW YOUR BOAT'S
IN THE MARINA?

17:19.167 --> 17:20.909
-MM-HMM. OBSESSION.

17:21.083 --> 17:22.998
-[LAUGHS]
-THAT'S HER NAME.

17:23.172 --> 17:24.086
AND SHE IS.

17:24.826 --> 17:26.306
I'D LIKE TO TAKE HER
AROUND THE WORLD, THOUGH.

17:26.480 --> 17:27.307
-BY YOURSELF?

17:29.178 --> 17:30.310
-NOT NECESSARILY.

17:32.312 --> 17:34.488
TELL ME WHY A MAN LIKE YOU
IS STILL A LIFEGUARD.

17:35.793 --> 17:37.099
-MOST PEOPLE HATE
TO GO TO WORK.

17:38.274 --> 17:39.145
I DON'T.

17:39.797 --> 17:40.798
-I KNOW WHAT YOU MEAN.

17:41.582 --> 17:43.714
THAT'S WHY I DECIDED
TO GO INTO BUSINESS FOR MYSELF.

17:44.628 --> 17:46.761
NO PARTNERS
AND NO BOSSES.

17:48.023 --> 17:49.590
-WHAT ABOUT
YOUR INVESTORS?

17:50.417 --> 17:51.896
-WELL, I'VE ALREADY
PAID BACK ONE OF THEM.

17:52.071 --> 17:53.333
AND WHEN I PAY
BACK THE OTHER,

17:54.073 --> 17:56.466
I'LL HAVE COMPLETE
AND TOTAL FREEDOM.

17:57.293 --> 17:59.904
-NO ATTACHMENTS...
FROM ANYONE.

18:03.343 --> 18:05.171
-WHAT DO THEY SAY
IN CHINA?

18:06.215 --> 18:09.262
"YOU SAVE MY LIFE,
SO YOU BELONG TO ME?"

18:09.436 --> 18:10.785
OR "I BELONG TO YOU?"

18:13.309 --> 18:15.006
-I THINK IT'S
"YOU BELONG TO ME."

18:17.183 --> 18:18.575
-AND THAT'S AN ATTACHMENT,
ISN'T IT?

18:21.230 --> 18:23.363
YOU KNOW, THERE'S SOME
SWIMSUITS IN THE BATHHOUSE.

18:23.537 --> 18:25.016
DO YOU EVER SWIM
JUST FOR FUN?

18:25.191 --> 18:26.496
-[LAUGHS AWKWARDLY]

18:29.151 --> 18:30.500
I THINK IT'S TIME
FOR ME TO LEAVE.

18:33.242 --> 18:34.287
-WHY?

18:34.939 --> 18:36.332
YOU SAID YOUR SON
WAS WITH HIS MOTHER ALL WEEK.

18:36.506 --> 18:37.420
-YEAH. I KNOW.

18:40.510 --> 18:42.338
I JUST DON'T LIKE
STARTING SOMETHING

18:42.512 --> 18:44.079
WHEN I KNOW WHERE
IT'S GONNA END.

18:45.820 --> 18:46.647
-TRUST ME...

18:47.517 --> 18:49.432
YOU HAVE NO IDEA
WHERE THIS IS GONNA END.

19:39.830 --> 19:40.701
HEY, LIFEGUARD...

19:42.790 --> 19:44.052
WHAT ARE YOU WAITING FOR?

22:39.401 --> 22:40.707
-[CLINKING NOISE]

22:40.881 --> 22:42.709
-MITCH. MITCH.
-[GROANS]

22:42.883 --> 22:44.058
-THERE'S SOMEONE
IN THE HOUSE.

22:45.320 --> 22:46.582
-WHAT?

22:46.756 --> 22:48.105
-I HEARD A NOISE
IN THE LIVING ROOM.

22:51.674 --> 22:52.849
-WELL, COULD IT
BE THE OWNERS?

22:53.023 --> 22:54.198
-NOT WITHOUT CALLING.

22:54.373 --> 22:55.504
PLEASE GO
AND SEE WHO IT IS.

22:55.678 --> 22:57.158
-OKAY. OKAY.

23:12.086 --> 23:14.218
[GASPS]
-MITCH, BE CAREFUL.

23:14.393 --> 23:16.351
-OKAY. JUST WAIT FOR ME.

23:17.047 --> 23:18.222
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

24:54.014 --> 24:56.495
-[GUNSHOTS, CLANKING]

25:16.471 --> 25:17.516
-[GUNSHOT]

25:19.039 --> 25:20.083
-[THUD]

25:25.436 --> 25:26.655
-ARE YOU OKAY?

25:28.701 --> 25:29.702
-YEAH.

25:32.182 --> 25:33.314
I'M OKAY.

25:35.969 --> 25:37.318
-DID I KILL HIM?

25:49.460 --> 25:50.810
-YOU SHOT HIM
RIGHT THROUGH THE HEART.

25:56.467 --> 25:57.381
HE'S DEAD.

25:58.687 --> 26:01.908
-[GASPS]
-[GUN CLATTERS]

26:09.002 --> 26:09.959
-HEY, NOW.

26:15.530 --> 26:17.140
PROBABLY SAVED
A THOUSAND LIVES BEFORE,

26:17.314 --> 26:19.360
BUT THAT'S THE FIRST TIME
ANYBODY HAS EVER SAVED ME.

26:21.362 --> 26:22.798
-OH, GOD.
IF YOU WEREN'T HERE,

26:23.320 --> 26:25.018
IT WOULD'VE BEEN ME
DEAD ON THE FLOOR.

26:28.325 --> 26:29.500
-DO YOU KNOW
WHO HE IS?

26:30.414 --> 26:31.328
-YES.

26:34.331 --> 26:35.985
HE'S MY EX-HUSBAND.

26:38.466 --> 26:39.598
WHEN I LEFT HIM...

26:41.164 --> 26:42.383
HE THREATENED TO KILL ME.

26:47.344 --> 26:48.476
-WAS THAT WHY
YOU WANTED ME HERE?

26:48.650 --> 26:49.869
TO PROTECT YOU?

26:50.391 --> 26:53.437
-NO. I DIDN'T EVEN KNOW
HE FOLLOWED ME TO LOS ANGELES.

26:56.571 --> 26:59.705
BUT I DID KNOW
THAT I'D BE SAFE WITH YOU.

27:04.971 --> 27:05.885
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

27:06.059 --> 27:07.277
-I'M GONNA CALL THE POLICE.

27:09.715 --> 27:11.064
-MITCH, WAIT.

27:12.282 --> 27:14.850
BEFORE YOU CALL,
CAN WE TALK ABOUT THIS A SECOND?

27:16.330 --> 27:20.334
UM... WHAT IF THE POLICE SAY
THAT I SHOT MY HUSBAND?

27:20.508 --> 27:21.465
THAT I MURDERED HIM?

27:24.251 --> 27:25.992
-YOUR HUSBAND
OR YOUR EX-HUSBAND?

27:26.166 --> 27:27.254
-EX-HUSBAND.

27:29.125 --> 27:30.126
-THEY WON'T.

27:30.692 --> 27:32.085
HE BROKE IN,
HE HAD A GUN,

27:32.259 --> 27:33.782
HE WAS ABOUT TO SHOOT ME.
YOU HAD NO CHOICE.

27:37.656 --> 27:39.832
ALLISON, I'VE GOTTA
CALL THE POLICE.

27:41.921 --> 27:44.488
SO IF THERE'S ANYTHING
I SHOULD KNOW BEFORE I DO...

27:45.881 --> 27:47.013
TELL ME NOW.

27:49.842 --> 27:50.799
-NO.

27:51.974 --> 27:53.193
I'VE TOLD YOU EVERYTHING.

27:55.586 --> 27:56.457
-OKAY.

27:57.588 --> 27:59.503
-MITCH, YOU SHOULDN'T
GET INVOLVED IN THIS.

28:00.287 --> 28:01.767
YOU SHOULD GO.
I'LL CALL THEM.

28:02.637 --> 28:03.812
THERE'S NO NEED
TO GET INVOLVED.

28:03.986 --> 28:05.118
I AM INVOLVED.

28:05.814 --> 28:07.555
HEY, HEY.
YOU FORGOT.

28:08.599 --> 28:09.949
YOU SAVED MY LIFE, TOO.

28:10.906 --> 28:12.255
NOW WE BELONG
TO EACH OTHER.

28:53.340 --> 28:55.690
-SO WHAT ELSE
DID DETECTIVE CONNOR SAY?

28:55.864 --> 28:57.997
-THAT'S IT. MITCH STAYED
WITH HER AT THE POLICE STATION

28:58.171 --> 28:59.781
FOR MOST OF THE NIGHT
AND THEN HE SAID

28:59.955 --> 29:01.391
THAT HE WAS TAKING HER
BACK TO HIS HOUSE.

29:01.565 --> 29:03.654
-NOT GONNA PRESS CHARGES?
-NO. APPARENTLY NOT.

29:03.829 --> 29:05.134
-DON'T YOU THINK
THAT'S A LITTLE WEIRD?

29:05.308 --> 29:07.397
-WHAT?

29:07.571 --> 29:09.486
-WELL, THIS LADY IS WITH
TWO GUYS IN TWO DAYS
AND THEY BOTH END UP DEAD.

29:10.313 --> 29:11.358
NOW SHE'S WITH MITCH.

29:27.809 --> 29:32.292
-♪ I'VE BEEN WAITING FOR THIS MOMENT ALL
OF MY LIFE ♪

29:34.816 --> 29:38.733
♪ AND I WANT YOU TO KNOW THE WAY I FEEL ♪

29:41.910 --> 29:46.349
♪ DON'T YOU KNOW THERE'S A FIRE BURNING
INSIDE OF ME ♪

29:47.698 --> 29:52.573
♪ SO LET'S TAKE ON OUR FANTASY TONIGHT ♪

29:52.747 --> 29:54.488
♪ YOU'RE ALL THAT I WANTED ♪

29:55.619 --> 29:58.100
♪ YOU'RE ALL THAT I NEED ♪

29:59.798 --> 30:01.974
♪ I'LL MAKE THAT PROMISE ♪

30:02.626 --> 30:08.154
♪ TO STAY FAITHFULLY ♪

30:08.850 --> 30:11.287
♪ FAITHFULLY ♪

30:20.731 --> 30:23.430
♪ IF THERE'S A CHANCE TO TAKE THIS LOVE, ♪

30:23.604 --> 30:25.606
♪ LET'S MAKE IT TONIGHT ♪

30:27.564 --> 30:32.178
♪ LET ALL THE FEARS IN THE PAST JUST DRIFT
AWAY ♪

30:34.789 --> 30:39.446
♪ CAN'T YOU SEE THERE'S A STORM STILL
BUILDING INSIDE OF ME ♪

30:40.882 --> 30:45.844
♪ SO LET'S MAKE IT OUR FANTASY TONIGHT ♪

30:46.018 --> 30:48.324
♪ YOU'RE ALL THAT I WANTED ♪

30:48.498 --> 30:51.501
♪ YOU'RE ALL THAT I NEED ♪

30:52.938 --> 30:55.375
♪ I'LL MAKE THAT PROMISE ♪

30:55.549 --> 30:58.421
♪ TO STAY FAITHFULLY ♪

30:59.770 --> 31:02.295
♪ YOU'RE ALL THAT I WANTED ♪

31:02.469 --> 31:08.388
♪ SO WON'T YOU BELIEVE ♪
♪ AND STAY WITH ME ♪

31:09.432 --> 31:11.870
-I THINK THIS IS THE MOST
WONDERFUL TIME I'VE EVER HAD.

31:14.002 --> 31:16.483
AND YOU ARE THE MOST GENUINE,

31:16.657 --> 31:18.572
MOST PASSIONATE MAN
I'VE EVER MET.

31:27.015 --> 31:29.322
-ALLISON, I THINK I'M FALLING--
-MITCH, PLEASE DON'T.

31:32.760 --> 31:34.240
MITCH, I HAVE TO SAY GOODBYE.

31:39.941 --> 31:40.855
-WHAT?

31:41.856 --> 31:42.901
-I'M SORRY, MITCH.

31:43.075 --> 31:44.250
IF THINGS WERE DIFFERENT...

31:44.424 --> 31:45.512
-WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

31:48.341 --> 31:49.559
-SOUTH ON OBSESSION.

31:49.733 --> 31:51.387
MAYBE MEXICO OR BRAZIL.

31:53.128 --> 31:55.174
SOMEWHERE FAR AWAY
FROM EVERYTHING HERE.

31:57.654 --> 31:58.568
-INCLUDING ME?

32:01.658 --> 32:02.746
-WHY DON'T YOU COME WITH ME?

32:03.878 --> 32:05.488
-YOU KNOW I CAN'T
COME WITH YOU.

32:07.186 --> 32:09.057
-YOU ONCE SAID YOU DIDN'T
WANT TO START SOMETHING

32:09.231 --> 32:10.319
WHEN YOU KNEW
WHERE IT WOULD END.

32:11.973 --> 32:13.148
YOU WERE RIGHT.

32:14.628 --> 32:17.239
IF YOU COME WITH ME,
WE'LL BE TOO MUCH IN LOVE
TO SAY GOODBYE.

32:18.675 --> 32:20.416
LET'S JUST SAY IT NOW
WHILE WE STILL CAN.

33:11.511 --> 33:13.252
-[CAR ENGINE STARTS]

35:03.579 --> 35:05.233
-DETECTIVE CONNOR:
SO WHEN EDDIE
VOICED HIS SUSPICIONS,

35:05.407 --> 35:07.322
I HAD A CORONER
RE-EXAMINE THE BODY.

35:07.496 --> 35:09.542
A STEVE PIERCE
DROWNED ALL RIGHT...

35:09.716 --> 35:11.326
BUT NOT IN THE OCEAN.

35:12.022 --> 35:14.155
-HIS LUNGS WERE FILLED
WITH CHLORINATED WATER.

35:14.329 --> 35:16.766
-SO HE WAS ALREADY DEAD
WHEN THAT CAR WAS DRIVEN

35:16.940 --> 35:17.985
OFF THE CLIFF.

35:18.681 --> 35:20.596
-MAYBE HE WAS SWIMMING
BEFORE THE CRASH

35:20.770 --> 35:22.120
AND SWALLOWED SOME WATER.

35:22.294 --> 35:24.687
-HE DID!
ENOUGH TO DROWN.

35:25.297 --> 35:26.559
-TELL HIM ABOUT THE WRIST.

35:26.733 --> 35:28.387
-YEAH, THERE WERE
MARKS ON HIS WRIST

35:28.561 --> 35:30.693
THAT INDICATED THAT HE HAD BEEN
HANDCUFFED BEFORE HE DIED.

35:30.867 --> 35:32.782
-THAT'S RIGHT. THEN I FOUND
HANDCUFFS IN HER SUITCASE.

35:34.219 --> 35:35.350
-WHAT THE HELL WERE YOU DOING
LOOKING THROUGH HER SUITCASE?

35:35.524 --> 35:36.830
-I DIDN'T TRUST HER.

35:37.004 --> 35:38.353
-SO YOU WENT THROUGH HER THINGS?
-FELLAS--

35:38.527 --> 35:39.789
-MITCH, SHE WAS USING YOU
TO PROTECT HER.

35:39.963 --> 35:41.574
-HER EX-HUSBAND
WAS TRYING TO KILL HER!

35:41.748 --> 35:43.750
-IT WASN'T HER EX-HUSBAND.
IT WAS HER PARTNER.

35:45.055 --> 35:45.926
-THAT'S RIGHT.

35:46.622 --> 35:48.972
HE WAS A CON MAN
NAMED DREW LAWRENCE.

35:50.365 --> 35:52.976
LOOKS LIKE SHE PUT
YOU RIGHT IN THE MIDDLE
OF A DOUBLE-CROSS.

35:53.151 --> 35:54.848
-I DON'T BELIEVE ANY OF THIS.
-DON'T?

35:55.022 --> 35:56.415
OR DON'T WANT TO?

36:10.994 --> 36:13.083
-YOU KNOW, I HAVE TO
BRING HER IN FOR QUESTIONING.

36:16.435 --> 36:18.132
-SHE SAVED MY LIFE.

36:18.306 --> 36:20.090
-SHE'S THE ONE WHO PUT YOU
IN DANGER IN THE FIRST PLACE.

36:21.222 --> 36:22.267
-WHERE IS SHE, MITCH?

36:33.016 --> 36:34.366
-WHAT'S TAKING CONNOR SO LONG?

36:34.540 --> 36:35.976
DO ME A FAVOR
AND CHECK ON HIM, WILL YA?

36:49.598 --> 36:51.992
-[BEEPING, ENGINE STARTS]

36:59.304 --> 37:00.218
-HEY! MITCH!

37:00.827 --> 37:01.958
-SORRY!

37:04.396 --> 37:05.962
THIS IS SOMETHING
I GOT TO DO MYSELF.

38:15.684 --> 38:17.251
-[BOAT SIREN WAILS]

38:22.648 --> 38:23.736
-LOWER YOUR SAILS!

38:23.910 --> 38:25.215
-GO BACK, MITCH!

38:26.086 --> 38:27.914
DON'T MAKE THIS HARDER
THAN IT ALREADY IS!

38:28.088 --> 38:30.395
-I SAID LOWER YOUR SAILS.

38:31.134 --> 38:32.353
I'M COMING ABOARD.

38:41.536 --> 38:42.450
SIT DOWN.

38:45.018 --> 38:46.628
DID STEVEN PIERCE DROWN
IN A SWIMMING POOL?

38:46.802 --> 38:47.716
YES OR NO?

38:50.023 --> 38:51.067
-YES.
-[GASPS]

38:53.505 --> 38:54.636
WAS HE HANDCUFFED?

38:55.420 --> 38:56.334
-YES.

38:57.073 --> 38:58.727
HE KILLED HIMSELF, MITCH.

38:58.901 --> 39:01.339
HE KILLED HIMSELF BECAUSE
I TOLD HIM I WOULDN'T MARRY HIM.

39:04.080 --> 39:06.082
I WENT OUT TO THE POOL
AND HE ALREADY HANDCUFFED

39:06.256 --> 39:07.954
HIMSELF TO THE BOTTOM RUNG
OF THE LADDER.

39:08.868 --> 39:10.348
I-- I PANICKED.

39:10.522 --> 39:12.524
HE WAS MARRIED.
WE HAD AN AFFAIR.

39:12.698 --> 39:13.786
IT ENDED.

39:14.395 --> 39:15.918
I DIDN'T KNOW
WHAT ELSE TO DO.

39:17.224 --> 39:18.747
I PUT HIS BODY IN THE CAR.

39:19.879 --> 39:21.663
I WAS GONNA
BURY HIM AT SEA.

39:23.273 --> 39:26.494
I GOT SCARED
AND I STARTED TO CRY.

39:27.930 --> 39:29.932
THAT'S WHEN I DROVE
THE CAR OFF THE CLIFF.

39:33.501 --> 39:34.459
-SO EVERYTHING
FROM THE BEGINNING

39:34.633 --> 39:35.590
HAS BEEN A LIE, HUH?

39:35.764 --> 39:36.939
EVERYTHING?

39:37.113 --> 39:38.550
-NO. NOT EVERYTHING.
-ALLISON...

39:38.724 --> 39:40.552
-NOT THE WAY
I FEEL ABOUT YOU.

39:40.726 --> 39:42.075
THAT'S NOT A LIE--
-I'VE COME
TO TAKE YOU BACK, ALLISON.

39:43.381 --> 39:44.512
-I WON'T GO.

39:46.340 --> 39:48.603
-IF YOU'RE TELLING THE TRUTH,
YOU'VE GOT NOTHING
TO BE AFRAID OF.

39:49.996 --> 39:51.911
-WHAT DO YOU KNOW ABOUT FEAR?

39:52.825 --> 39:54.870
WHAT DO YOU KNOW
ABOUT BEING MANIPULATED

39:55.044 --> 39:56.655
BY PEOPLE
WHO WANT TO CONTROL YOU?

39:56.829 --> 39:59.005
-A HELL OF A LOT MORE NOW
THAN I DID A FEW DAYS AGO.

40:00.354 --> 40:03.052
-I WILL NEVER LET
ANOTHER MAN RUN MY LIFE.

40:05.620 --> 40:06.534
NOT EVEN YOU.

40:24.422 --> 40:25.205
I DON'T WANT
TO KILL YOU, MITCH.

40:25.379 --> 40:26.249
BUT I WILL.

40:27.250 --> 40:28.817
-SAME WAY
YOU SHOT YOUR PARTNER?

40:29.644 --> 40:30.732
THROUGH THE HEART?

40:31.907 --> 40:33.518
-YOU LEARNED A LOT
IN A SHORT TIME.

40:33.692 --> 40:35.911
-WHAT DID THE TWO OF YOU
CON STEVE PIERCE OUT OF ANYWAY?

40:36.608 --> 40:38.610
WAS IT MONEY?
REAL ESTATE?

40:38.784 --> 40:41.308
-YOU'RE MAKING IT HARDER
TO LET YOU GO, MITCH.

40:41.482 --> 40:42.527
-AW.

40:43.310 --> 40:45.573
AS HARD AS IT WAS WHEN
YOU SAID YOUR TEARFUL GOODBYE?

40:46.531 --> 40:47.314
WOW.

40:47.488 --> 40:49.098
WHAT A PERFORMANCE.

40:49.272 --> 40:51.013
-PLEASE DON'T MAKE ME DO THIS.

40:51.187 --> 40:53.233
-WOULD YOU RATHER PUT
A HANDCUFF TO MY WRIST?

40:55.714 --> 40:56.715
DROWN ME?

40:59.282 --> 41:01.502
-I'LL SHOOT.
I PROMISE I WILL.

41:03.504 --> 41:04.462
-I DON'T BELIEVE YOU.

41:22.480 --> 41:23.393
-ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

41:23.568 --> 41:24.438
-YEAH.

41:26.658 --> 41:28.529
-DO I STILL
BELONG TO YOU, MITCH?

41:30.618 --> 41:31.663
-NO.

41:35.928 --> 41:36.668
YOU BELONG TO HIM.

41:36.842 --> 41:38.147
-LET'S GO.

41:44.153 --> 41:45.024
-MITCH...

41:50.508 --> 41:52.335
IS THIS THE WAY
YOU THOUGHT IT WOULD END?

41:53.075 --> 41:53.946
-NO.

42:11.703 --> 42:12.704
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

42:12.878 --> 42:14.488
-I WANT TO SEE
WHAT'S IN HERE.

42:17.404 --> 42:19.014
SO THIS IS WHAT
IT WAS ALL ABOUT.

42:19.188 --> 42:20.276
-I GUESS SO.

42:39.644 --> 42:41.907
-[END MUSIC PLAYING]
